{
  "stem": "14897.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I was saying, my life was still a life of, relatively speaking, a privileged person, because my father was making a living.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And most of my friends' parents-- people who came from Warsaw were, of course, better off than the people who came from the surrounding little towns and villages who had been dispossessed overnight with whatever they could carry and brought to the Warsaw ghetto with very few possessions.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Life in the ghetto was a life of contrasts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We have contrasts here between people who are poor and people who are very wealthy, but you have to bring it to a totally different level.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You were rich if you could eat and had a room to live in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When you were poor, you were homeless.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You had nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Every morning when we came out into the street, we would see corpses lying on the-- on the ground in the streets, people who had died overnight from starvation and later on also from typhus, which was a big epidemic in the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We lived-- the-- the clinic where we lived, the windows were on the street.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you could see a corner, at which there was one of the official gates to the ghetto of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So from my window, I could look at the activities at this border crossing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This was manned by both German-- I don't know, police, SS, gestapo, something like that-- and Poles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you could see groups of Jewish children in the morning trying to run through out of the ghetto, because they would go and try to beg, steal, buy some food and smuggled it back in the evening into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
